    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix bounds checking error in TDD channel measurement unpacking\n\n### Summary\nThe `unpack_tdd_channel_measurement_value` function in nfapi_p7.c had incorrect bounds validation that could cause buffer overreads when processing malformed SRS indication messages. The function would proceed with unpacking even when the reported number of subbands or antennas exceeded maximum supported values.\n\nThis fix strengthens the validation checks and ensures proper error reporting.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Enhanced bounds checking with proper error logging\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Added validation for num_prb_per_subband field\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen processing SRS indication PDUs with malformed TDD channel measurement TLVs containing:\n- number_of_subbands > NFAPI_MAX_NUM_SUBBANDS (13)\n- num_atennas > NFAPI_MAX_NUM_PHYSICAL_ANTENNAS (8)\n- num_prb_per_subband set to invalid values\n\nThe unpacking function would previously return success but leave the structure in an inconsistent state. Now properly returns error codes and logs descriptive messages.\n\nObserved symptom was incorrect channel quality reporting in COTS UE testing scenarios.\n"
}